EXAMPLE PLAN (for subtask "Storage layer — In-memory repository with CRUD"):
CLASSES:
  class Repository:
    def __init__(self) -> None  # initializes dict[str, dict]
    def create(self, collection: str, id: str, data: dict) -> dict  # raises DuplicateKeyError
    def read(self, collection: str, id: str) -> dict  # raises NotFoundError
    def update(self, collection: str, id: str, data: dict) -> dict  # partial merge
    def delete(self, collection: str, id: str) -> None  # raises NotFoundError
    def list(self, collection: str, filter_fn: Callable | None = None) -> list[dict]
  class DuplicateKeyError(Exception): ...
  class NotFoundError(Exception): ...
DATA FLOW:
  create → validate id uniqueness → store copy in _data[collection][id] → return stored
  read → lookup → raise or return copy
  list → iterate collection → apply filter_fn → return list
TESTS:
  - test_create_and_read: round-trip create then read
  - test_create_duplicate_raises: DuplicateKeyError on same id
  - test_delete_then_read_raises: NotFoundError after delete
  - test_list_with_filter: filter_fn selects subset
  - test_update_partial_merge: only specified keys changed
DEPENDENCIES: none (self-contained)

